==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foraminifera
<hw>Fo*ram`i*nif"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>foramen</ets>, <ets>-aminis</ets>, a foramen +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive
order of rhizopods which generally have a chambered calcareous shell
formed by several united zooids. Many of them have perforated walls,
whence the name. Some species are covered with sand. See
<er>Rhizophoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foraminiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
